The paper discusses a framework for managing class schema evolution in persistent object-oriented software systems. This topic falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and database (cs.DB) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the design and implementation of the ESCHER system, which involves programming language concepts (cs.PL) and machine learning techniques (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the empirical studies conducted to evaluate the framework, which could fall under the human-computer interaction (cs.OH) sub-category.
